description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/ble_ipsp_transport.c
Lines: 586-599

In lichen_ble_transport_deinit():

    void lichen_ble_transport_deinit(void)
    {
        if (!transport_state.initialized) {
            return;
        }

        lichen_ble_transport_stop();  // May block waiting for disconnect

        k_mutex_lock(&transport_state.lock, K_FOREVER);
        transport_state.initialized = false;
        k_mutex_unlock(&transport_state.lock);

        LOG_INF("BLE transport deinitialized");
    }

Issues:
1. lichen_ble_transport_stop() is called without the mutex held
2. Between stop() and lock(), another thread could call send() or other APIs
3. After setting initialized = false, any pending callbacks (connected_cb, etc.) that fire could access partially-deinitialized state

The BLE callbacks (connected_cb, disconnected_cb, etc.) are registered globally via BT_CONN_CB_DEFINE and will continue to fire even after deinit.

Fix: The deinit should disable callbacks or check initialized flag at the start of each callback.
